>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.insight.rr.com/meridianxev/images/Meri2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> Hello all,<br><br>For almost 55 levels, I've lived with the most disorganized spellbook you can imagine.  Basically, with each spell level, I've just dumped the spells into the book in no particular order whatsoever.<br><br>With the new UI, I'd like very much to organize my spell book in some manner that makes sense.  I have managed to move all the port/succor/evac spells to their own pages, but the rest of it just - ugh - I don't know where to start!<br><br>So what I'm looking for is advice and suggestions, and perhaps some examples of how others have their spellbooks organized.<br><br>I appreciate any and all feedback.  Thanks!<br><br>Meridian Ascendant<br>54 Wanderer of Xev <p><center><italic>And I gave that guy directions even though I didn't know where it was cuz that's the kind of guy I am...Homer Simpson</center></italic></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Hierophant<br><center>of The Grove</center></span><br>  Posts: 2052<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 2:16:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> Here is one efficient setup, that requires the least amount of page flipping to get the job done:<ul><li>Put spells that you <i>swap in and out the most</i> in the beginning of the book.  You can separate these out into 2 pages of buffs and 2 pages of offensive spells, or whatever order makes sense to you.  The idea is that when you want to swap spells in and out in combat you can do it quickly without fumbling around.  Don't put spells you always have memorized (e.g., Ensnare) in this area, as it's a waste.  (If you want to get fancy, you can put the <i>most</i> used spells on pages 3 and 4, and the second-most used spells on pages 1 and 2 and 5 and 6, and set your spellbook hotkey to go to page 3, so that 6 pages of spells will be no further than 1 page flip away.)<br><li>After that, put spells that you always have memorized, but would need to memorize after death.  This could be your main heal, snare, and DD.  You don't want this up front because you only need to access it on death (in fact, it could be even later on in the book).<br><li>After that, put all of your Circle spells, in whatever order pleases you, followed by Ring spells (preferably, have the order of Circle spells match that of Ring spells, so that you can find them easily).  These aren't used as frequently and almost never need to be accessed in an emergency.<br><li>After that, put rarely used but not totally obsolete spells, e.g., Banishment and Glamour of Tunare.<br><li>After that, I traditionally put a "twink page", with spells that I don't normally use but can be cast on players below level 45.  If you never use such spells, you can skip this step.<br><li>I leave a blank page or two after that (room for future expansion), then all of the useless, outdated, and obsolete spells.  If you're really anal (who, me?), you can organize the useless, outdated, and obsolete spells if you ever want to use them in the future for testing.</ul>I'd post a screenshot of an example but servers are down... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=torinn>Torinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 2:38:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> A druids spell book is very large, i found that the best way to navigate is to hotkey your pages.  My spell book for example (now reorganized for the new ui) looks like this<br><br>Page 1 - 2 <br>Heals, Buffs, Resists, Cures<br>Hotkey - /book 1<br><br>Page 3 - 4<br>Nukes, Debuffs, DoTs, Group Effects<br>Hotkey - /book 3<br><br>Page 5 - 6<br>Rings<br>Hotkey - /book 5<br><br>Page 7 - 8<br>Circles<br>Hotkey - /book 7<br><br>Page 9 - 10<br>Misc (Invis, EB, See Invis, Egress, Succor, Wolf Form, etc)<br>Hotkey - /book 9<br><br>How you choose to organize it really isn't as big a deal as having the book mapped with hotkeys so when you need a spell and you need it 3 seconds ago *Click* You're on the right page w/ no flipping and searching. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gardener in the Grove<br>Admin au naturel</span><br>  Posts: 2237<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 2:50:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cityviewsoftware.com/jennifer/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> <img align=right src=http://www.cityviewsoftware.com/jennifer/actiongwyn35.jpg>I second what Tudamorf is saying. It's a spice rack kind of thing. You put your most used where you can reach them. So when I was organizing, I left a lot of room up front for new spells — for example, before I had Moonfire or Nature's Recovery, I left open slots on the first and third page. <br><br>You might want to start by moving your never-used spells from your lower levels way to the back. That's what I did, then I left like four blank pages in front of those so I'd never have to look at them again. Then I cleared out the first ten pages, reserving most-used buffs and damage spells to the front. I also left room for spells I didn't have back then like POTC. I organized all debuffs on the same page kind of near the front so I could swap them. I organized most-used Ring spells, then most-used Cirles, followed by rarely used Rings and Circles, and Succors. Gate and Succor are up front and not with Rings/Circles.<br><br>There's no right way, but the sure way to do better is to rearrange your book according to how you define "organization." Soloing druids and raid druids shouldn't have the same spellbook setup. :p<br><br>Hehe. Organizing my shaman's book was much harder and time-consuming.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 3:09:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> I only have one thing to add...<br><br>Work out how you plan to organize it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> before</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you move a single spell.... If you start shuffiling them around before you have decided just what goes where it is going to take you quite a bit longer to do the job. If you happen to have multiple caster's spellbooks to organize that extra time will really add up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Watcher of the Grove</span><br>  Posts: 401<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 4:48:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> The new spell book was a great opportunity for me to finally do the spring clean on my spell book I wanted to do.  Good to be forced to do it since it is so painful.<br><br>I can't add much to the theory that was posted above (great post btw) but I will share what I did (cuz I am kinda happy with it).<br><br>Page 1-2   Self / Single Target Buffs<br><br>Page 3   Group buffs (or buffs I tend to cast on other people - even if a little rarely)<br><br>Page 4  The heals and regens I actually use...with 2 open slots for where my wishes and dreams go (new heals new heals please)<br><br>Page 5-6   Cures and resists.  Also dumped the roots and snares here...a little odd but I remember and had the room<br><br>Pages 7-8 Nukes<br><br>Page 9  Dots and Debuffs<br><br>Page 10-15  Gates and Circles, organized side by side:<br><br>   Bind affinity   -   Gate<br>   Ring of Commons  -  Circle of commons<br>   Etc.<br>   Old world first, then expansion spells, then evacs and succors at the end<br><br>Page 16   Pet and pet buff spells, summon spells<br><br>All my actively used spells are in the first 16 pages.  Hopefully PoP will add a lot and I will have to work it all over again.<br><br>You really have to do what makes sense to you but figured I would share.  I picked up an idea here or there from others that I like and work it into my own layout...so passing mine along.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Hierophant<br><center>of The Grove</center></span><br>  Posts: 2055<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 5:34:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> Here's a concrete example of what I mean (these images are highly compressed under 20K each, should load pretty fast):<br><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook1.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook2.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook3.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook4.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook5.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook6.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook7.jpg><br><img src=http://lag9.com/spellbook8.jpg><br><br>Useful ones that are swapped in/out are kept towards the front, followed by death stuff, then circles/succor/rings, then not-so-useful spells, then twink stuff.  Obsolete and crap spells I just left out.  Also looking at my spellbook, I think my babysitter forgot to get the greater remove curse spell... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 7/31/02 5:35:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ua4mula.showPublicProfile?language=EN>a4mula</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 5:36:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> I use the first 8 slots to put my most used spells.  Then I'll start sorting back from utilities (see invis, invis, EB, lev ect), Then Rings, Circles, Group Spells, I keep all of my old spells (skin like wood, light heal ect) on page 40 so they're never in the way.  Also make sure to make socials.  Name em Rings and put /book 3, or whatever the case maybe for quick access to what you are looking for.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uglorybme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glorybme</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.glorysite.com/eq/images3/gloryspin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Might be Housebroken</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#333399>(7/31/02 6:25:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28027.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.glorysite.com/eq/images3/gloryb3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook Reorganization</span><hr size=1> <a href=http://www.glorysite.com/eq/spells.html target=_blank>My level 60 spell book</a> the new one. Also, not that I alphbetized my circle and ring spells. This is the first time I did that but since all the spell icons are in rows, unlike old spellbook, and I love it that way. So much quicker to find the correct port.<br><br>I left room for new spells and made a point of NOT cluttering the pages by trying to fill all the spell slots, it helps me figure